    <section id="id8232599">
      <title>Assessment</title>
      <para id="id1166314039052"><emphasis><emphasis effect="italics">Assessment Standard 1.4:</emphasis></emphasis> We know this when the learner orders, describes and compares whole numbers to at least 2-digit numbers.</para>
      <para id="id1166313729075"><emphasis><emphasis effect="italics">Learning Outcome 1:</emphasis></emphasis>The learner will be able to recognise, describe and represent numbers and their relationships, and to count, estimate, calculate and check with competence and confidence in solving problems.</para>
      <para id="id1166310215142"><emphasis><emphasis effect="italics">Learning Outcome 1:</emphasis></emphasis>The learner will be able to recognise, describe and represent numbers and their relationships, and to count, estimate, calculate and check with competence and confidence in solving problems.</para>
      <para id="id1166314214572"><emphasis><emphasis effect="italics">Assessment Standard 1.9:</emphasis></emphasis> We know this when the learner uses the following techniques:</para>
      <para id="id1166318364571">1.9.1 building up and breaking down numbers;</para>
      <para id="id1166313536060">1.9.2 doubling and halving;</para>
      <para id="id1166314921908">1.9.3 using concrete apparatus (e.g. counters);</para>
      <para id="id3975705">1.9.4 number-lines.</para>
    </section>
